# Master Rules

This file serves as the central reference for all Cursor rules in the repository.
This file makes it easier for the AI agent to find the discover rules when they are organized in folders.

## How to Use Rules

### For AI Agent Behavior

- Use [agents/cursor_rules.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/agents/cursor_rules.mdc) when managing or creating new cursor rules
- Use [agents/commit_summary.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/agents/commit_summary.mdc) when generating commit messages
- Use [agents/rule_usage.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/agents/rule_usage.mdc) to track which rules were applied

### For Code Quality and Standards

- Use [guidelines/markdown.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/guidelines/markdown.mdc) when writing or editing markdown files
- Use [guidelines/naming.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/guidelines/naming.mdc) when creating or updating files and folders
- Use [guidelines/import_export.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/guidelines/import_export.mdc) when working with module imports and exports

### For Specific Workflows

- Use [commands/extract_frontmatter_from_markdown.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/commands/extract_frontmatter_from_markdown.mdc) when extracting frontmatter from markdown files
- Use [commands/generate_changeset.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/commands/generate_changeset.mdc) for creating and managing changeset files in the monorepo
- Use [commands/generate_commit_message.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/commands/generate_commit_message.mdc) when writing commit messages

### For Templates

- Use [templates/cursor_rules.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/templates/cursor_rules.mdc) when creating new cursor rule files

